eval("__webpack_require__.r(__webpack_exports__);\n/* harmony export */ __webpack_require__.d(__webpack_exports__, {\n/* harmony export */   editorSandboxSamples: () => (/* binding */ editorSandboxSamples),\n/* harmony export */   getEditorSandboxInitialDocuments: () => (/* binding */ getEditorSandboxInitialDocuments)\n/* harmony export */ });\n/** Images under `/editor-sandbox/*.svg` are placeholders only; companies and metrics are fictitious. */ const editorSandboxSamples = [\n    {\n        id: \"team-inbox-refresh\",\n        label: \"Team Inbox Refresh\",\n        teaser: \"Fictitious case with narrative, process blocks, and illustrative outcomes.\",\n        document: {\n            metadata: {\n                title: \"Team Inbox Refresh\",\n                slug: \"team-inbox-refresh\",\n                summary: \"Fully fictitious sample: shows how a case can go from context to execution with editorial blocks and a live preview. No client, product, or outcome here is real.\",\n                publishedAt: \"2025-02-14\",\n                company: \"Nimbus Desk Ltd.\",\n                role: \"Lead Product Designer\",\n                platforms: \"Web app\",\n                domain: \"Internal tools\",\n                tags: \"Sandbox, Editorial system, Collaboration\",\n                coverImage: \"/editor-sandbox/sandbox-cover-queue.svg\"\n            },\n            content: `# Context\n\nIn this **fictitious** scenario, a support team had visibility into incoming work, but not enough structure to understand what was urgent, what was blocked, and what needed follow-up.\n\n<Callout title=\"Sandbox note\" variant=\"insight\">\nAll names, numbers, and screenshots here are invented for the public editor sandbox. They do not describe a real engagement.\n</Callout>\n\n# Process\n\n<ProcessTimeline\n  title=\"Project rhythm\"\n  items='[{\"title\":\"Audit\",\"period\":\"Week 1\",\"description\":\"Mapped the inbox states that created uncertainty for triage leads.\"},{\"title\":\"Prototype\",\"period\":\"Week 2\",\"description\":\"Tested a denser card layout with clearer status, ownership, and timing cues.\"},{\"title\":\"Refinement\",\"period\":\"Week 3\",\"description\":\"Tuned hierarchy, motion, and copy so the queue stayed scannable under pressure.\"}]'\n/>\n\nThe goal of the editor experience is to let the story stay structured without breaking the visual narrative of the case page.\n\n<GalleryGrid\n  columns=\"2\"\n  items='[{\"src\":\"/editor-sandbox/sandbox-detail-1.svg\",\"alt\":\"Fictitious queue audit placeholder\",\"caption\":\"Illustrative placeholder — not a real product screen.\"},{\"src\":\"/editor-sandbox/sandbox-detail-2.svg\",\"alt\":\"Fictitious card iteration placeholder\",\"caption\":\"Illustrative placeholder — not a real product screen.\"}]'\n/>\n\n# Outcome\n\n<ImpactResults\n  title=\"Illustrative impact (not measured)\"\n  summary=\"Metrics below are dummy values to show the block only. They are not from a real study.\"\n  metricOneLabel=\"Triage time\"\n  metricOneValue=\"-28%\"\n  metricOneNote=\"Fictitious median time to first assignment\"\n  metricTwoLabel=\"Escalations\"\n  metricTwoValue=\"-17%\"\n  metricTwoNote=\"Fictitious reduction between teams\"\n  metricThreeLabel=\"Confidence\"\n  metricThreeValue=\"+21 pts\"\n  metricThreeNote=\"Fictitious self-reported confidence\"\n/>\n\n<PullQuote\n  quote=\"This quote is invented for the sandbox so you can see how pull quotes render in the layout.\"\n  author=\"Alex Rivera\"\n  role=\"Fictitious operations lead, Nimbus Desk Ltd.\"\n/>\n`\n        }\n    },\n    {\n        id: \"restaurant-discovery\",\n        label: \"Restaurant Discovery\",\n        teaser: \"Fictitious sample with Figma embed, TOC, and editorial sections.\",\n        document: {\n            metadata: {\n                title: \"Restaurant Discovery Flow\",\n                slug: \"restaurant-discovery-flow\",\n                summary: \"Fictitious example to show richer sections, embeds, and navigation. Company, flows, and dates are invented; there is no real product behind it.\",\n                publishedAt: \"2025-01-08\",\n                company: \"Copper Spoon Labs\",\n                role: \"Product Designer\",\n                platforms: \"Marketplace\",\n                domain: \"Food & hospitality\",\n                tags: \"Sandbox, Figma, Storytelling\",\n                coverImage: \"/editor-sandbox/sandbox-cover-marketplace.svg\"\n            },\n            content: `# Opportunity\n\nIn this **made-up** story, users could tell when their first restaurant choice was unavailable, but the product did very little to help them confidently pick an alternative.\n\n<TOC\n  title=\"In this sample\"\n  items='[{\"id\":\"opportunity\",\"label\":\"Opportunity\"},{\"id\":\"prototype\",\"label\":\"Prototype\"},{\"id\":\"handoff\",\"label\":\"Handoff\"}]'\n/>\n\n# Prototype\n\n<Figure\n  src=\"/editor-sandbox/sandbox-detail-3.svg\"\n  alt=\"Fictitious high-fidelity placeholder\"\n  caption=\"Illustrative placeholder image — not a real interface from a shipped product.\"\n/>\n\n<FigmaEmbed\n  url=\"https://www.figma.com/design\"\n  title=\"Figma embed (sandbox)\"\n  caption=\"Minimal URL only to show the empty state without an iframe — no real file is attached.\"\n/>\n\nThe paired editor and preview make it easier to understand not just the final layout, but also how the page is assembled from shell metadata and authorable body blocks.\n\n# Handoff\n\n<VideoEmbed\n  url=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aqz-KE-b5KQ\"\n  title=\"Big Buck Bunny (open movie — embed demo)\"\n/>\n\n<Callout title=\"About the video\" variant=\"default\">\nWe use a short **Big Buck Bunny** clip (Blender Foundation, CC-licensed) only to demonstrate the video embed block — it is unrelated to the fictitious story above.\n</Callout>\n`\n        }\n    },\n    {\n        id: \"design-review-kit\",\n        label: \"Design Review Kit\",\n        teaser: \"Short fictitious sample: quick edits, metadata, and blocks.\",\n        document: {\n            metadata: {\n                title: \"Design Review Kit\",\n                slug: \"design-review-kit\",\n                summary: \"Compact, entirely invented sample: for showing quick edits, metadata, and per-section selection. None of this corresponds to a real project.\",\n                publishedAt: \"2024-11-04\",\n                company: \"Atlas Loop Studio\",\n                role: \"Senior Designer\",\n                platforms: \"Design system\",\n                domain: \"Collaboration\",\n                tags: \"Sandbox, Review, Components\",\n                coverImage: \"/editor-sandbox/sandbox-cover-review.svg\"\n            },\n            content: `# Setup\n\nThis sample is intentionally compact so the visitor can quickly see the preview react to small edits in the editor. **All content is fictional.**\n\n<Figure\n  src=\"/editor-sandbox/sandbox-detail-5.svg\"\n  alt=\"Fictitious design review board placeholder\"\n  caption=\"Illustrative placeholder — not a real critique session or product UI.\"\n/>\n\n<Callout title=\"Try editing this\" variant=\"insight\">\nChange the title, tags, overview, or section heading from the inspector to see how shell and body stay aligned.\n</Callout>\n\n# Assets\n\n<GalleryGrid\n  columns=\"2\"\n  items='[{\"src\":\"/editor-sandbox/sandbox-detail-2.svg\",\"alt\":\"Fictitious review board placeholder\",\"caption\":\"Illustrative placeholder — not a real review board.\"},{\"src\":\"/editor-sandbox/sandbox-detail-4.svg\",\"alt\":\"Fictitious UI detail placeholder\",\"caption\":\"Illustrative placeholder — not a real interface.\"}]'\n/>\n\n# Result\n\n<ImpactResults\n  title=\"Illustrative metrics\"\n  summary=\"Values below are dummy numbers for layout preview only.\"\n  metricOneLabel=\"Review prep\"\n  metricOneValue=\"-35%\"\n  metricOneNote=\"Fictitious time saved before reviews\"\n  metricTwoLabel=\"Decision clarity\"\n  metricTwoValue=\"+18 pts\"\n  metricTwoNote=\"Fictitious confidence after sessions\"\n/>\n`\n        }\n    }\n];\nfunction getEditorSandboxInitialDocuments() {\n    return Object.fromEntries(editorSandboxSamples.map((sample)=>[\n            sample.id,\n            sample.document\n        ]));\n}\n//# sourceURL=[module]\n//# sourceMappingURL=data:application/json;charset=utf-8;base64,\n//# sourceURL=webpack-internal:///(ssr)/../../portfolio-main/packages/editor/src/sandbox/sandbox-samples.ts\n");

